<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4496816>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 5. Terminology used for descriptions of chaetae and anal cirri of Phyllodoce. A, compound spinigerous chaeta; B, anal cirri cylindrical, with tapered distal rounded and scar pygidial cirri (black arrow); C, anal cirri cylindrical, with tapered distal ends; D, anal cirri cylindrical, with tapered distal end; pigidial papilla (black arrow). Scale bars: A, 0.01 mm; B, 0.15 mm; C, 0.25 mm; D, 0.04 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4496816/files/figure.png" .

