<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4496810>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 3. Terminology used for species description of Phyllodoce. Dorsal view of proboscis: A, proboscis divided into two parts: 1, terminal ring; 2, distal part of proboscis; 3, proximal part of proboscis; 4, nuchal papilla. Formulae and morphology of the tentacular cirri. Cirri formula: (B) 1 + 2 + 1=First pair of dorsal tentacular cirrus; 2=Second pair of ventral and dorsal tentacular cirri; 1=Third pair of dorsal tentacular cirrus. Cirri morphology; B, cylindrical, anterior view; C, cylindrical ventral cirrus with lateral lamella; D, cylindrical ventral cirrus with inflated base. Abbreviations: Dc, dorsal tentacular cirrus; Vc, ventral tentacular cirrus. Scale bars: A, 0.5 mm; B, 0.8 mm; C–D, 0.5 mm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4496810/files/figure.png" .

